File: A health worker shows a vial of the Chinese-made Sinopharm COVID-19 vaccine. AFP/Ishara S Kodikara JOHANNESBURG - Good news on the COVID-19 vaccine front. Sahpra is testing the efficacy of the Sinopharm jab. READ: Zimbabwe begins vaccine rollout with Sinopharm jabs The manufacturers of the Chinese vaccine applied to the South African regulatory body to authorise emergency use. It's the second Chinese vaccine -- after Sinovac -- being tested by Sahpra. READ: Russia says Sputnik V virus vaccine 92% effective The Russian-made Sputnik vaccine is also being investigated. There've been battles between vaccinologists and the COVID-19 Ministerial Advisory Committee on which vaccines to use in South Africa.